MBOMBELA &#8211; Book lovers are in for a treat later this month, when Lowvelder&#8217;s Pen in my Hand initiative will host Bridget Hilton-Barber, the well-known travel writer and author, to present her memoir.Hilton-Barber, who is based in Limpopo, has worked as a travel correspondent and editor in her colourful career in the South African media. Student Comrade Prisoner Spy is her ninth book.The chilling account of her experience during the apartheid years chronicles how she became politically involved in anti-apartheid organisations and the resistance movement in the Eastern Cape, as a rebellious young student at Rhodes University in the early 1980s.READ MORE: Pen in my hand: Bridget Hilton-Barber will be talking about her new book